reviews.name: WWendy Dy
reviews.text:
WORST EXPERIENCE DOING MY INVISALIGN HERE! First and last time.

The doctor seemed to be inexperienced and I felt that I was her “first patient”, even though with all her promises and talking at the initial consultation.

I felt CHEATED. The whole process from start to finish felt super rushed, uncomfortable, and most importantly I felt UNHEARD as their patient.

During each arrangement of appointments, I would always come early before my designated time. Most of the times I have to wait for the doctor for more than 20 minutes up to 40 minutes even! Only to be brushed off with a weak apology. The lateness repeated in most of my appointments. I am so disappointed with their poor punctuality.

Also, be prepared that your appointment will get cancelled or changed last minute without early notice. Arrangements of appointment seems to be the most difficult with this dental clinic. Punctuality and customer service is not what I would think of this clinic.

It was a NIGHTMARE during my last day of Invisalign where she was removing the brackets from my tooth, it was EXTREMELY PAINFUL and she was rushing to finish without even bothering about my pain! Everything felt rushed and messy! She even polished and chipped off one of my tooth and it turned out disproportionate and smaller than my original tooth!

My bite wasn’t even too, I couldn’t close my bite and it was a HUGE issue which should be fixed during my whole Invisalign treatment. I pointed out the problem to her, she just brushed it off and said it was not an issue. I felt unheard and felt disrespected. I guess ending her shift earlier and going back home was her only concern in her mind.

The outcome of my teeth wasn’t even satisfying and didn’t look as expected, I went to other dental clinics to only to be pointed that my teeth had a lot of issues including the bite problem I mentioned! I had to do another set of Invisalign at another clinic to fix it as they clearly saw the problems too.

Also, there were hidden fees after my whole treatment was finished. Was promised with free scaling during my consultation, only to be slapped on the bills with fees charged on it. I insisted to discuss the matter with them over WhatsApp but they denied. Bear in mind the receptionist was incredibly rude and disrespectful. After that the “hidden charges” was only to be chased by them through phone calls after 6 months out of no where, what a joke.

I seriously felt my money, trust and 2 years were wasted at this T Care Dental clinic. Well, all the negative experiences here, I got the whole package 🤷‍♀️.

I feel that it’s only justified that I put my words and experience here for those who plans on getting their Invisalign or treatments here. Think twice.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Hi Wendy,

We have thoroughly reviewed our patient records and could not find your name listed. All of our Invisalign patients have consistently expressed satisfaction with their treatment, and we take great pride in the quality of care we deliver.

We also observed from your Google profile that you previously liked SEPA Dental Puchong—our neighboring clinic—and were publicly thanked by them under the name “Kelly Cheng” approximately 11 months ago. This raises some doubt about the validity of your claim of being our patient for the past two years.

It’s possible that you may have contacted us at some point and received an automated reminder message, but a screenshot of such a message does not serve as confirmation of an ongoing treatment relationship. If you have indeed received treatment at our clinic, we kindly ask you to provide more concrete details such as appointment dates or receipts so that we can verify and address your feedback appropriately.

We can proudly say that the majority of our patients are undergoing braces, Invisalign, or other clear aligner treatments. Our patients are genuinely happy and satisfied with their treatment progress and outcomes, and their continued trust in our services is what drives us to do our best every day.

We are always open to honest, constructive feedback—but we also take misrepresentation seriously and respectfully ask for accuracy and fairness in all reviews.

Thank you

I had a scary dental experience when I was a child.

We went to YN Chan Dental Surgery again. The dentist there is an experienced and gentle dentist.

The doctor will predict that the next treatment will be a bit painful, and will inject an anesthetic before proceeding with the treatment. He will also inform us of the discomfort of the next treatment and give us psychological preparation.

The dentist is very gentle during treatment. She will carefully observe our reactions, adjust the frequency to a low level, and try to make us relax as much as possible.

The dentist will also give us some advice and dental care knowledge. Let us pay more attention to the condition of our teeth in the future. 👍

She cured my dental phobia. 😁

Datang klinik pukul 6.53 pagi parking masih banyak. 6.58 pagi start beratur dah ada 10 orang kat depan. 7.15 dah beratur panjang sampai ke laluan berbumbung. 7.30 pagi dah boleh naik atas untuk ambil nombor. Beratur kejap kat tangga sementara staf setup.

7.50 pagi dah start panggil nombor. 7.55 pagi nombor kena panggil pergi dekat kaunter untuk pendaftaran sebab first time datang. Bayar RM1 (card only). 8.05 pagi nama kena panggil untuk check tekanan darah. 8.10 pagi dah masuk bilik rawatan. Kita bagitahu sakit apa, Dr check dan explain berkenaan condition gigi. Dr bagi pilihan untuk buat rawatan apa untuk sesi kali ni sebab setiap sesi 1 rawatan je boleh buat. Dr akan tanya keselesaan kita bila dah selesai.

8.25 pagi dah selesai dan pergi kaunter untuk bayar. Saya bayar RM4 untuk servis tampal 2 gigi. Dr buat 2 gigi terus sebab sebelah-sebelah. Biasanya boleh rawat 1 gigi je setiap sesi. 8.30 pagi dah settle semua dan boleh balik.

reviews.textTranslated:
Came to the clinic at 6.53 in the morning and there was still plenty of parking. 6.58 am start queuing, there are already 10 people at the front. 7.15 there was a long queue until the covered passage. 7.30 am can go upstairs to take the number. Queue for a moment at the stairs while the setup staff.

7.50 am already started calling the number. 7.55 in the morning the number had to be called and went to the counter for registration because it was the first time to come. Pay RM1 (card only). 8.05 am name to be called to check blood pressure. 8.10 am entered the treatment room. We tell you what the pain is, the doctor checks and explains about the condition of the teeth. Dr. gave me the choice of what treatment to do for this session because only 1 treatment can be done for each session. Dr will ask about our comfort when it is finished.

8.25 am finished and went to the counter to pay. I paid RM4 for the filling service of 2 teeth. Dr made 2 straight teeth because they are side by side. Usually only 1 tooth can be treated per session. 8.30 am everything is settled and you can go back.

I think the service here is okay and satisfactory. But remember, first come first serve. If you come late, you have to wait a long time for your turn. Dr and staff are okay 👍🏻

reviews.name: Narendranath Ramana
reviews.text:
I visited 32T Dental for what was supposed to be a simple molar tooth surgery.
Removing a molar is never easy—it demands skill, patience, and a deep sense of care. Yet, from the moment I stepped in, everything felt surprisingly calm, almost as if I was exactly where I was meant to be.

By a stroke of luck, I found myself under the care of Dr. Neoh Ein Yau.
A wonderful soul—calm, gentle, and deeply professional. His soft voice, steady hands, and reassuring smile washed away every ounce of fear. He didn’t just treat a tooth; he treated a human being—with dignity, patience, and heart. For that, I am profoundly grateful.

Thanks to the sophisticated equipment and Dr. Neoh’s vast experience, the procedure unfolded with incredible smoothness and comfort.
There was no struggle, no discomfort—only a quiet confidence in the air, like a symphony played by a master. In that peaceful half-hour, my mind drifted elsewhere.

As I lay silently in the chair, memories of my late mother rose within me like a soft, unspoken prayer.
“Naren, please brush your teeth before you sleep,” she would say with a smile, night after night.
“Don’t eat sweets—they will spoil your teeth,” she would remind me, her voice filled with a tenderness only a mother can give.
Those simple words, once brushed aside by my youthful stubbornness, now echoed louder than ever in my heart. In that moment, her love wrapped around me like an invisible blanket.

A mother’s love never dies.
It lingers quietly—in our small habits, in fleeting thoughts, in the spaces between heartbeats. She gave so much, asked for so little, and loved without conditions. Years later, her gentle spirit still walks beside me, unseen but deeply felt—like a hand resting lightly on my shoulder.
What once felt like mere reminders now feel like sacred truths.
In that quiet chair, I realized: love like hers never leaves you. It becomes part of who you are.

So often we think we know better—we ignore their words, thinking we’ll figure it out ourselves.
But life has a way of circling back, teaching us with gentleness and sometimes with tears, that mothers always knew best.

Returning to the present, I couldn’t help but notice how special 32T Dental was.
Every staff member, from the front desk to the nurses, carried themselves with such grace and warmth.
They didn’t just provide a service—they gave comfort, kindness, and care, in a world that often forgets how badly we all need them.

Dr. Neoh Ein Yau, though perhaps 15 years my junior, treated me with a reverence usually reserved for someone’s father.
His voice was soft, his words full of respect. His kindness was never hurried, never mechanical—it was sincere and effortless.
He explained every step with the patience of someone who truly understood human fears.
There was a quiet dignity in the way he worked, a rare and beautiful thing in today’s fast-paced world.
In that moment, age, titles, roles—none of it mattered. What mattered was the connection between two human beings, built on respect and compassion.

It is extraordinary how a simple dental visit turned into a profound life moment.
Not pain, but peace.
Not fear, but reflection.
Not discomfort, but overwhelming gratitude.

To Dr. Neoh, his wonderful team at 32T Dental, and above all, to the enduring, everlasting love of my late mother—
Thank you. Thank you from the depths of a heart that will never forget.

When planning and monitoring orthodontic treatment with braces, several types of dental X-rays are commonly used to provide detailed information about teeth, jaws, and surrounding structures. Each type serves a specific purpose in ensuring the treatment is effective and safe.

1) Panoramic X-Ray
- Identifies impacted, missing or extra teeth.
- Evaluates jaw structure and bone health.
- Detects any underlying conditions, such as cycsts or tumors.

2) Lateral Cephalometric X-Ray
- Diagnosing bite problems (e.g. overbite, underbite)
- Helps plan jaw alignment and tooth movement.
- Provides a basis for analyzing facial growth and symmetry.

3) Frontal Cephalometric X-Ray (needed in certain cases only)
- Allow precise evaluation of facial and skeletal symmetry.
- Identifies whether teeth overlap incorrectly in a lateral 
  direction.
- Evaluate jaw position.

𝗔𝗰𝗿𝘆𝗹𝗶𝗰 𝗗𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲𝘀: Acrylic dentures are among the most widely used types of dentures due to their affordability, easy customization, and natural appearance. They are also relatively simple to adjust or repair if they become loose or damaged.

𝗖𝗼𝗯𝗮𝗹𝘁 𝗖𝗵𝗿𝗼𝗺𝗲 𝗗𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲𝘀: Cobalt chrome dentures are valued for their strength, durability, and lightweight properties. I recently visited Tiew Dental Bandar Puteri for a dental checkup, the Dr. Gan Wei Chien informed me about a tooth decay that required filling. I agreed to proceed with the filling immediately. To my dismay, the new dentist revealed that the filling at Tiew Dental Bandar Puteri was improperly done, leaving the root exposed and resulting in an infection. As a consequence, I now need a root canal treatment to salvage the tooth, which could have been avoided had the initial procedure been performed correctly.

I am very disappointed with the level of care I received at Tiew Dental by Gan Wei Chien. The apparent negligence has not only caused me additional pain and inconvenience but also a more complicated and costly treatment. I can not recommend this clinic based on my experience.
